{"paperId": "61b5fda1416a7c7362e7ff7511fdcd54a82b339a", "title": "UM-IU@LING at SemEval-2019 Task 6: Identifying Offensive Tweets Using BERT and SVMs", "abstract": "This paper describes the UM-IU@LING\u2019s system for the SemEval 2019 Task 6: Offens-Eval. We take a mixed approach to identify and categorize hate speech in social media. In subtask A, we fine-tuned a BERT based classifier to detect abusive content in tweets, achieving a macro F1 score of 0.8136 on the test data, thus reaching the 3rd rank out of 103 submissions. In subtasks B and C, we used a linear SVM with selected character n-gram features. For subtask C, our system could identify the target of abuse with a macro F1 score of 0.5243, ranking it 27th out of 65 submissions.", "venue": "International Workshop on Semantic Evaluation", "year": 2019, "citationCount": 37, "influentialCitationCount": 2, "openAccessPdf": {"url": "https://www.aclweb.org/anthology/S19-2138.pdf", "status": "HYBRID"}, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "The UM-IU@LING\u2019s system for the SemEval 2019 Task 6: Offens-Eval takes a mixed approach to identify and categorize hate speech in social media."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [0.23455995321273804, 0.7754176259040833, -0.5137462019920349, 0.14967256784439087, -0.055958982557058334, -0.5336685180664062, 1.0191941261291504, 0.1412256509065628, -0.1955207735300064, -0.14517083764076233, 0.39189907908439636, -0.43301185965538025, 0.685964047908783, 0.38634759187698364, -0.0018512309761717916, 0.15378424525260925, -0.5154123306274414, 0.24136291444301605, -0.40779510140419006, -0.012447326444089413, 0.16908761858940125, -0.792648434638977, -0.5114736557006836, 0.4874686896800995, 0.44120335578918457, 0.6471569538116455, -0.6292237639427185, 0.79205721616745, -0.1963231861591339, 0.5879568457603455, -0.1974019557237625, -0.7688474059104919, 0.23614154756069183, 0.1980813890695572, -0.4691692292690277, -0.11254949867725372, 0.5836521983146667, -0.80805373191